The paper deals with the evaluation of ranking algorithms, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses user ranking and recommendation systems, which are related to artificial intelligence (AI) and human-computer interaction (HC), respectively. Finally, the paper presents results on constructed and real data sets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
